14/05/2007
PODGORICA, Montenegro -- Slavica Milacic, Montenegro's ambassador to the EU, said at the weekend that the signing of a Stabilisation and Association Agreement with the EU could be expected in October. 
The document, initialled during EU Enlargement Commissioner Olli Rehn's visit to Podgorica in March, is now being translated into all official EU languages. 
Given the upcoming summer holidays, fall is the likely timeframe for signing, she said.
In other news, a Montenegrin delegation including government representatives and members of parliament wrapped up a two-day visit to NATO headquarters in Brussels on Friday. 
The focus was on reforms that must be implemented in line with membership in the Partnership for Peace programme. 
(Mina - 14/05/07; Pobjeda - 12/05/07)
